section.section:
In addition to the powers set forth elsewhere in this subtitle, the EMS Board may:
Subject to the limitations set forth in § 13-509 of this subtitle, adopt regulations to carry out the provisions of this subtitle;
Create committees from among its members;
Appoint advisory committees, which may include individuals and representatives of interested public or private organizations;
Apply for and accept any funds, property, or services from any person or government agency;
Make agreements with a grantor or payor of funds, property, or services, including an agreement to make any study, plan, demonstration, or project;
Except for confidential medical information, publish and give out any information that relates to the delivery of emergency medical services and is considered desirable in the public interest;
Hold public hearings; and
Set and charge reasonable fees to be paid by the applicants for the designation of trauma and specialty referral centers.
